Special committee formed to probe the killings in Mtwara and Kilindi in Tanga region has submitted reports to Prime Minister Kassim Majaliwa. Speaking after receiving Mtwara and Tanga dossiers on Friday, the Premier congratulated the committee for discharging its duties diligently. After going through the submitted reports, the Premier has promised to submit them to the Head of State, who directed him to form the committee. Majaliwa said theÂ President Samia wants "objective reports which will hold culprits into account." The committee, which began work on the matter on February 4, 2022, was due to complete its report within 14 days, or February 17, 2022. Instead, the committee requested an additional seven days citing the magnitude of the assignment to complete it efficiently.